PLEASE turn your sound ON and press the "Keep Watching" button to view these posts, see all of the photographs and hear the stories. I've been getting many notes from folks who wonder where all my pictures have been the past few weeks. They are here, just in a new way. So, thanks for taking a minute to watch and please let me know what you think of this format. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
I'm often asked, Hey Vince, what's your next BIG IDEA for The Year of the Dogs? ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
And I think, well, I've made a bestselling book that captured the hearts of dog lovers around the world—created an award-winning box set of greeting cards that are loved by generations and published a very successful 2021 dog calendar, if you take cats out of the equation. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
So I look back over this pandemic year, and I have no regrets. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
I've been to bed, bath, and beyond. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Last week I had a virtual brunch with my close friends George Clooney and Ryan Reynolds and The Rock. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
While none of them have authored a book on dogs, they each gave me some tough love and entrepreneurial advice for my next step. I want to thank them as - Today, I proudly Introduce you to The Year of the Dogs Wine Club. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Exclusively for followers of this account. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Yes, The Year of the Dogs Wine Club. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Not like those snobbish around-the world-in-50 bottles-of-Malbec wine clubs, because this one is created by Dogs for Dogs. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Seen here are just some of the distinguished members of our certified panel of Advanced and Master Sommelier dogs. These dogs have highly sophisticated olfactory receptors and great palates. Each painstakingly seeks out the best wines that dogs can buy. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Has your dog ever come home with an overpriced, bad bottle of Barolo? ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
The Year of the Dogs Wine Club solves that problem with extensive tasting notes tailored to your breed's likes and dislikes. Our dogs' sniff, slurp, swig, swirl, and spit, so you don't have to. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Because if our dogs don't like it, you won't get it. It's just that simple. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Our dogs take their work very seriously, but they love the work. Sometimes too much. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Rest assured, we are working on that. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Have a great week. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
#WineClub #winelover

⁣⁣
⁣⁣
The following is from a recently declassified National Security report filed by 7-year-old Charlie, an Airedale mix who is known to exaggerate. .⁣⁣
⁣⁣
“I was abducted.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
On the morning of September 1, I was taken to a large metal building that looked like a spaceship. Inside was a white room where a giant cloth hung down from the ceiling.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
It smelled like dog in there.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
There were two “people” inside with mostly human features, a male and a female, and they were very friendly to me. The woman was tall, and the most incredible bacon-flavored food came directly out of her fingertips. The man did not speak at first.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Both wore surgical masks like you see in a hospital.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
I remember I couldn’t feel my legs and then realized I was being lifted in the air and placed on a small examination table. More bacon-flavored food shot out from the woman’s fingertips. The man approached with a one-eyed machine or probe that he pointed in my direction. He spoke to the woman telepathically and waved his arms. He also smelled like dog. I was content to eat the bacon-flavored food and engage in small talk with the woman.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
At some point, and I’m not clear about what happened, but a bright light filled the room, and I felt light-headed. It was then that I realized the bearded man was pointing the one-eyed-probe thing at me and then the room went bright again. It was like lightning or fireworks but we were still inside the ship.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
I began to leave at this point but was detained by some invisible force. I didn’t understand why the people weren’t leaving too, as this shaft of light was life-threatening for all of us. I then saw the bright light again, and it felt like I was outside of my body looking down at myself, and I felt really hairy and craved brisket.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
It was then that I realized I may have been tricked in some way, lured by the food and the “good boy” baby talk. After the 3rd bright light, I was able to get away safely. I woke up later in the backseat of my car half remembering all of this, but I couldn’t be sure as I had no evidence.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Later I pooped, and it all came back to me.”⁣⁣
⁣⁣
#MuttsOfInstagram #UFO #InterviewsWithDogs

node.text:
Annabelle⁣⁣
⁣⁣
If The Year of the Dogs ever made it to Broadway, the Grande Dame known professionally as Annabelle would be our leading lady. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
It’s often said that the great thespians own the stage. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Her rare blend of animal magnetism, quick wit, and self-confidence was on display in a recent performance at our studio as she went through a range of roles and personalities for us. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
She’s a physical actress but not overpowering. Her asides were gentle and charming, her characters honest and rich with integrity. Callie and I were overcome with emotion and found it challenging to photograph and applaud at the same time. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
We laughed and we cried. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Annabelle got her big break late in life by auditioning for her local college drama club. Her career was delayed by previous commitments and a traveling troupe of scene-stealing heartworms. Once freed of the contractual obligations, her career has taken off. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
She’s often typecast as a middle-aged suburban Staffordshire Terrier, the house pet turned action-hero, saving the world from invading squirrels and meddling chipmunks. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Given a choice, Annabelle prefers more traditional roles where she plays the mothering figure to young children in the mold of a Maggie Smith or Judy Dench, always lending a sympathetic ear but with an ulterior motive only the audience is aware of. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Bravo, Annabelle. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Have a great week. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣

Good Morning.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
How are you today? ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Welcome to The Unleashed Studio, where we photograph beautiful dogs and make beautiful photographs of them, every single day.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
I’m your host Vince Musi, and it’s a beautiful day on Instagram isn’t it? ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
This week we’re in our studio with Cooper, Ziggy and Jagger and you can plainly see things are going very well. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Beautifully well, if I may.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Because what’s more beautiful than one beautiful dog? ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Three. Yeah. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
You can see just how much the dogs are enjoying it. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
How much they love the staying and the sitting, and the waiting, and the posing. ⁣⁣

⁣⁣
I have long been afraid of photographing Jack Russell Terriers, regardless of how many eyes they may or may not have. This is not meant to unfairly malign Rocco or his spirited bloodlines; it’s just that One-eyed Jacks are always wild. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Now, that paragraph came to me in my sleep after we photographed Rocco. It was chasing a ball around in my subconscious, and I jumped out of bed to scribble it down before it was lost to the after-effects of the wine that Callie and I drank earlier. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
When these spirited epiphanies come to me in the middle of the night, I like to wake Callie up and run the line by her, like a stand-up comedian practicing new material at a comedy club. Callie pretends to be asleep and says she doesn’t hear me calling her. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
10 year-old Rocco lost the eye not seen here, to a run-in with a Cat. 
He was a much younger man then but holds no grudges now that I’m aware of. He makes perfectly good use of his remaining eye, which can still be seen here. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Rocco is a damn good dog who never sleeps or stops, even to pee or eat. He’s in a state of perpetual motion, slowing only to calculate wind-speed and change direction. More than that, he would never pretend to be asleep, no matter how bad my jokes were. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Have a great week. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Rocco is in The Year Dogs, a book that is mostly about dogs but not always. Since we didn’t have much of a book tour, I thought you might enjoy this version. Thanks for sticking with us. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
#jackrussell #dogs

⁣⁣
⁣⁣
I have always wanted to change my name to be more successful. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
You can read all of the big-thinker, 7-highly-effective, self-help books you want,  but it all comes down to your name, and the less name you have, the better, as in just one name. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Mononymous. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
I think about Thor, Homer, Madonna, Sting, Charo, and Pele. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
All fairly successful leaders in their respective fields or realms, and although it’s hard to go wrong with Thor or God of Thunder, you have to admit Cherilyn Sarkisian or Shawn Corey Carter aren’t exactly catchy names like Cher or Jay-Z. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Of course, you have to work hard to live up to a short name. It doesn’t always work out, think of poor Hamlet. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Barto lives up to his one name. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
While his given name is something of a mystery, it was likely as long and complicated as is his breeding and backstory. You see, just 5 months ago, Barto was a man of the road, and the road was not very forgiving no matter what his name might have been. Mange, starvation, and a swerving pickup truck nearly ended his 6-year career. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Today, Barto is a success story. A civic leader, an earnest gentleman who is cheerful and thoughtful, especially when it comes to the desires of a stuffed animal he fancies that goes by the name Unicorn. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Have a great week. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
#TheYearOfTheDogs

⁣⁣
⁣⁣
We interrupt this post to bring you an update. ⁣⁣
For those of you just tuning in, I learned that a Cat Calendar was outselling my Dog Calendar in the Dog Calendar category. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
That’s right -Cats. In the dog category. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
I’m not cat shaming, but don’t we have enough going wrong at the moment?⁣⁣
⁣⁣
The dogs featured in my dog calendar blame me for this. They’re pointing paws, flooding my inbox with angry notes and trolling me on social media. Smokey is upset about his hair and Clyde thinks his butt looks too big. The Basset Hound siblings, Bullet and Shug have threatened legal action, accusing me of exploiting their image by making their ears look too big. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
For some reason Tolliver, the French Bulldog is unhappy with MARCH and DEMANDS to be on September now. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Finn, the handsome Golden Retriever known informally as “Mister September” refuses, but he’s tried to play peacemaker and put out a statement this morning calling for canine unity. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
I should note that the Cats aren’t taking this lying down either. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
I’ve been banned from a number of Cat Calendar Facebook Groups and apparently my name is now poo on a private Reddit forum dedicated to the subject. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Some Cats will stop at nothing. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Since going public on Sunday, I’m pleased to report, the Dogs are winning - but the battle continues. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
I’m in seclusion until all this blows over but remain eternally grateful for your continued support of the dogs and The Year of the Dogs Calendar. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
I say vote your heart. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Thank you. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
The Year of the Dogs 2021 calendar can be found wherever high-quality dog calendars are sold like Chronicle Books, Amazon and Barnes & Noble or click the link in my profile. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
#dogsofinstagram

Capers, revisited⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Dogs follow me. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
You may be aware that quite a few followers of this Instagram account are dogs. 

I'm humbled by their kind words and support, yet some of them, I suspect, are fake accounts run by people, not dogs. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
I'm not sure of their motives, but they're easy to spot. Seeing the caption "Frens, my Hooman is Jus Pawfect" is often a dead giveaway of a fake account. Dogs, trading in Bitcoin futures or penny stocks, are suspect. And, anything with a bulldog is likely a fake, as we all know, they tend to prefer Twitter. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Capers does not have his own social media account as he does not legally meet the minimum height and age requirements, but he is a real dog. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
He's a teacher's pet. This isn't mentioned in a pejorative "Lisa Simpson" sense; his adopted mother is a real teacher. Capers is a homeschooled lad who never claimed that a dog ate his homework although he's blamed a few missed deadlines on a local cabal of house cats. That said, he's quick to raise a paw, even if he doesn't know the answer to the question. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
"I do cute pretty well, but I don't let it go to my head. I work hard every day to prove I can use my intelligence and creativity, as well as my striking good looks. I'm a small dog with big dreams. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Sure, I've been stepped on by the big dogs, but who hasn't? Maltipoos are risk-takers and not afraid to get dirty or bark when we have to. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
I really enjoy working with people." ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Have a great week. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Thanks for sticking with us here. I hope to see you next week with more from #TheYearOfTheDogs or whatever else I can think up between now and then. ⁣⁣

Lucy⁣⁣
⁣⁣
We are leaving the city limits with a bulldog that is not our own. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
This is not our first rodeo. The dog is chill, but my navigator and loyal wife Callie is nervous, so we are cranking up a Lady Gaga playlist to keep her calm. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Rah, Rah, Ah, Ah, Ah, Roma, Roma, Ma, Gaga, Ooh La La…⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Minutes later we deliver the dog safely to their rightful owner. Mission Accomplished and another successful day in the life of semi-professional dog photographers. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Our door-to-door “white glove” service is not guaranteed, but so far, we’ve never kept a dog that wasn’t ours. As dog photographers, we abide to a strict code of conduct to not hoard other people’s dogs. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Good thing for Lucy. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
She’s a lovely, 7-year-old French Bulldog whose eyes and body language said take me home. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Which was more about her longing for a seat upon her favorite couch than any relationship she wanted with me. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
It’s been said that Lucy could remain up there for hours and perhaps days or probably weeks because what goes up does not always come down, whether it be furniture, stairs or beds. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Lucy has mastered the art of jumping up but will not jump down. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Have a great week. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣

node.text:
Cooper⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Everyone knows the high-stakes world of dog photography is fast-paced and challenging. To remain competitive, I’m on the lookout for a big-time sponsor like all those famous cat photographers have. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Don’t you think it’s about time? ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
I do get offers. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
 “Let’s together offer your followers something special and memorable that will strengthen their relationship with your brand!” promised the email from a perfume company. They offered to create my personal fragrance, a “unique scent” with a “splash of my aesthetic,” and give me 30% of the profits! ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
I was feeling pretty special and 30% more memorable until Callie, my loyal wife and chief dog whisperer, asked, “Who would actually pay to smell like a wet dog? ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
So, until a better offer comes along, I’m moving forward with my latest idea – The Sign of the Dogs®, selling advertising on the sides of dogs for local retail businesses. The dogs would wear cute little outfits and hats promoting things like auto repair and orthodontics. I would even pay them to strut around the dog park and pass out flyers for discount teeth-whitening and oil changes. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
I approached Cooper with the idea of wearing an ad for The Year of the Dogs. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
He’s a sturdy, athletic, 9-year-old Schnocker, which, for the layman, is concocted from a secret recipe of Miniature Schnauzers, Cocker Spaniels, and 11 herbs and spices. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Cooper immediately shut me down. Said he’s an “artist,” and his body is not for sale. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Then he sniffed, took a step back, and stuck his tongue out at me. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
 “Dude, you smell like wet dog.” ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Have a great week. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣

node.text:
The Unleashed Studio⁣⁣
⁣⁣
I never thought I’d be an inside dog. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
If I ever went missing, those who knew me best would never think to look for me inside of a studio, yet here I am in the good graces of an old canvas, kind wooden boards, and polite dogs. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Now in our 4th year, The Year of the Dogs began in a space behind a local pet supply store, wedged between pallets of dog food. From there, we moved into an old Sears warehouse until it became a fancy distillery which forced us to move into a converted cigar factory before it became a suite of offices. From there, we joined up with some cool kids, creative types and used a space surrounded by surfboards, skateboards, and motorcycles until the band broke up. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
The dogs liked these studios, and so did we. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
None of them were really designed for what we were aiming to do, but all became home for us and a creative place to celebrate the nobility, grace, and character of these incredible animals we share our lives with. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Today’s post is a tribute to those magical places and an optimistic toast to our new studio. Yes, we have found a new home! So, until this one becomes a hair salon or hookah bar, we are thrilled to be photographing dogs once again. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
If you are interested in coming to our Charleston, SC studio, send an email to hello@TheUnleashedStudio.com, and we’ll tell you how to get on our schedule. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Finally, Thank you so much for your kind words of encouragement and support of our work. Callie and I are truly humbled to be a small part of your lives each week. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
May the dogs be with you. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
These dogs were photographed in all of our old studios - Miles Davis, Bear, Ms. Sally, Monty, Luka, Bruno, Macho, Bullet Bliss and Dove, Gerdie, and a look at our Huger Street Studio from 2018 where we did most of our first book. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣

node.text:
Dexter⁣⁣
⁣⁣
I thought for sure I wasn’t going to make it here today. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Too much to do!  Like all of you with places to go and people to see, I’m a busy semi-professional dog photographer and completely out of gas. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
This week we lost our studio space and had to move again. Broken record, I know, but it’ll be a furniture store by the time you read this, and I feel like Harrison Ford in The Fugitive, always on the run with a pack of wild dogs chasing me. It’s hard to find humor when you’re the focus of a nationwide manhunt led by a pissed-off Tommy Lee Jones and a posse of deputized Labradoodles. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
I’m beginning to crack. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Week after week, you knew this would happen. It was bound to. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
I also missed the premiere of the new Fast & Furious movie. Yes, I let Vin Diesel down, and I was about to do the same to Dexter, this sweet 14-year-old Dachshund, who was unlikely to forgive me as Vin has on so many occasions. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Dexter’s smile got to me. “Pick me,” he said, “and share me with your millions of loyal and influential friends on Instagram before it goes all TikToky - while it’s still a thing.” ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
You can’t say no to that smile. Or the head tilt or the howling, barking, or side-eye. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
So, let me introduce Dexter, a small dog that is slightly smaller and shorter than your average Dachshund, two toes smaller to be precise, and part of a tail shorter to be kind. He lost the toes to cancer and the once considerably larger tail to an even larger car door. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
It should be noted that in selecting his color, Dexter couldn’t settle for any single one, choosing multiple as one does when presented with that option. His coat resembling a melted soft-serve twist-cone from your local ice cream stand, decorated with Jimmies or Sprinkles depending on your geographic allegiances. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Have a great week. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣

Hobbes⁣⁣
⁣⁣
In an effort to remain your #1 trusted source on @Instagram for dog photos and made-up stories about my life, I’m honored to present Hobbes, a 4-year-old Labrador Retriever who is entirely real and needs no fictional account of her life or clever anecdote from mine. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Hobbes embraces herself as she is. A fresh face on the Retriever scene, she is this season’s “It Girl” with a healthy natural glow, confident stride, and a winning smile. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Understated and humble, she does not wear makeup or use any sort of foundation to create her look, and these photographs are entirely unretouched. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Hobbes shuns designer fashion, expensive handbags, and fancy shoes, choosing just a simple collar and casual leash when she leaves the house. She does not employ a stylist except for the occasional visit to the salon. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Her luminous skin is a testament to regular hydration and sunscreen. This girl’s sweet demeanor is reflective of her indulgence in selectively curated Hall & Oates records from the 70’s, and 80’s. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Have a great week. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣

node.text:
Anubis, revisited⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Anubis is a massive 5-year-old rescued Great Dane who might easily outweigh your average high-school senior. She is a gentle, loving, and shy creature who can be afraid of her own shadow, particularly when said shadow is cast by a large piece of photographic lighting equipment. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Those of you familiar with the alternate dimension known as ‘The Upside Down’ from the science fiction television series Stranger Things will understand what it might be like for a dog to enter our studio. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
I could easily be mistaken as the predatory Demogorgon, a grunting humanoid covered in dog hair who sprawls on the floor with a large camera discharging a lightning storm through an array of studio flashes. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
It requires a huge leap of faith on a dog’s part to trust us – a leap that can be directly measured by their level of food motivation or interest in chasing a squeaking, neon-colored tennis ball around a cavernous warehouse. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
It doesn’t always go smoothly. This is where Callie, my first assistant, loyal wife, and chief dog whisperer, takes control of the situation while I curl up in a ball, issuing statements about the end of my career to anyone who will listen. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
 These are just a few of the obstacles that even the most affable dog and a well-adjusted photographer must overcome together to make it in The Year of the Dogs. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Have a great week. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
This story can be found in the #TheYearOfTheDogs, my book that is mostly about #dogs but not always. It’s low-fat and gluten-free if you like that sort of thing and it’s usually available wherever you can find books about dogs.
⁣⁣

Sully and Charlie⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Presented here as a public service, the cousins' Sully and Charlie. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
They are not considered dangerous but if encountered, approach with extreme caution if you are in possession of anything that can be eaten or ingested. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Anything. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Both dogs are known Labradors, 4-year-old males with brown eyes, weighing between 65 and 70 pounds, and standing roughly 24" tall. Sully is distinguished by a lighter color fur, and Charlie bears a small birthmark on his forehead. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Known aliases are Sullivan and Charleston, but they will take on any identity to thwart law enforcement or blend in with a crowd. Both answer to the name Treat or Cookie. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Charlie is slightly younger but considered the brains of the operation. He’s an expert at opening locked doors, bank vaults, security gates, kitchen cabinets, or UPS packaging. Sully is the front dog for the duo and can be seen on multiple surveillance videos creating a diversion. Both have a preference for Mexican restaurants, authentic or not. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
They may identify themselves convincingly as DoorDash or UberEats drivers but under no circumstances should they be trusted as they never deliver the food. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Presently the dogs are under house arrest with electronic monitoring and are not permitted to leave without an escort. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Not that it matters. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Have a great week. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Stories like this can be found in #TheYearOfTheDogs, my book that is mostly about #dogs but not always. It’s usually available wherever books about dogs can be found.⁣⁣

node.text:
Dear Westminster Kennel Club Humans, ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
We, the undersigned dogs of The Year of the Dogs, strongly object that there isn’t a Best Tongue in Show category. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
We’ve seen your competition, and your dogs have tongues whether you want to admit it or not. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
For many years, we dogs have used our tongues for good and bad, yet there is no recognition for the good we bring to the world. How can agility or obedience be of any concern to you if you ignore the tongue? ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Is it because of the panting? The breath? The drool? ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Yes, we lick things. Sometimes that’s wrong, and maybe we do it too much, but there is so much more. Most of it can’t be printed here, though, but who doesn’t enjoy a good lick? Our people keep coming back for more. The French Bulldogs call it kissing. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
And unlike Cats, we are proud lappers, not little sippers, and our tongues are a joy, and they don’t feel like sandpaper either. Do you think it’s easy to lap up a bowl of water? Peanut butter? Try it sometime, friends. No spoons or straws. Cups are cheating. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Some of us were born with big tongues.  Yet we should celebrate all tongues regardless of size or if they are curly or spotted, rolled or pointed, because it’s more important what you do with your tongue (again, within reason) rather than just measuring them. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
So, let’s talk tongue. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
We await your response. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Respectfully, ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Rue⁣⁣⁣⁣
Levi⁣⁣⁣⁣
The Dude⁣⁣⁣⁣
Louis⁣⁣⁣⁣
Lilly⁣⁣⁣⁣
Shug⁣⁣⁣⁣
Zippy⁣⁣⁣⁣
JoJo⁣⁣⁣⁣
Ellie Bou⁣⁣⁣⁣
Ms. Sally⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Have a Great Week. ⁣⁣

node.text:
Murphy⁣⁣
⁣⁣
I’m crazy about Panda Bears. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
On lockdown, I binge-watched the Giant Panda Cam from @smithsonianzoo, hoping for a glimpse of the celebrity pandas Tian Tian, Mei Xiang, and Xiao Qi Ji. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
My friend Ami Vitale has spent a considerable part of her life photographing Giant Panda Bears for National Geographic. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Baby Pandas. Old Pandas. Dirty Pandas. Sleeping Pandas. Hungry Pandas. Bored Pandas. Pandas playing with other Pandas.  Ami even went around dressing like a Panda just to blend in, although I don’t think she does this anymore. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
When Murphy came into the studio, I thought, it’s our time to shine. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
He’s smart, adorable, and loved by all, like a Panda, but a dog.  All the better for me because I’d hate to start over with The Year of The Pandas at this point. Plus, you don’t want Ami mad at you and have her show up at your studio in a panda suit. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Murphy is a 3 1/2-year-old Border Collie worthy of all the attention but humbly chooses more of a leadership role. He’s a dog’s dog, an influencer, looked up to and followed closely, but would never endorse a skincare product or recommend the bamboo mojito. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
If he did, I would likely buy it. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Have a great week. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣

Toby⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Nadia’s Theme rang out from our portable Bluetooth speaker as an expectant crowd gathered in our studio. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
If he was nervous, he didn’t show it. Toby knew the material and had trained long and practiced hard for this day and his chance at #TheYearOfTheDogs glory. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
A hush fell over the room as he began his floor routine. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
As former Olympic hopefuls, my wife Callie and I quietly wept as the 4-year-old Standard Poodle acknowledged us with a smile and confidently tumbled through a series of handsprings, walkovers, somersaults, and cartwheels. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Ending with a triple-lindy-scissors-leap, he stuck the landing on the rarely seen Red Poodle Salto to the delight and astonishment of the judges. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
The crowd burst with applause. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
We all knew we had witnessed greatness. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Look out Tokyo. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Have a great week.⁣⁣
⁣⁣

node.text:
Sojo⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Our heartfelt thanks and gratitude to all  who offered kind words and support about the loss of our studio last week. We are truly humbled. And thanks to the generous help of a neighbor, we’re now working in a fantastic temporary space until it gets leased to a furniture store or hair salon. #TheYearOfTheDogs continues. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Sojo could care less. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
She hated our old studio. Some dogs did. Whether it was the décor or the lingering aroma of other dogs or the flashy lights or the beeping and clicking noises, she rated us in the category of “hated it.” ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
My apologies. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
For the record, it was never our intention to offend or startle. I know now that some of my movements, actions, anecdotes, singing, cursing, and pleading may have been misconstrued, and I apologize for this misconstruing. I’m trying to be a better photographer and a better person, and I will learn from this. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
I only hope Sojo can look back on the experience fondly when she gets a little older. Maybe laugh about it. She’s a puppy, just 1-year-old, and has her whole life ahead of her. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Why hold a grudge with me? How does a dog get a Yelp account anyway? Does anybody even read those reviews? ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
For those who can’t quite place her breeding, let’s just say yes, there’s been some. The list is deep, and it might be easier to say there’s no Chihuahua or Great Dane in her lineage. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Everything else is on the table. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
I hope this doesn’t offend. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Have a great week. ⁣⁣
